  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.9.21-stable\r\nOS & Version: Linux (Amazon Linux 4.14.193-149.317.amzn2.x86_64)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nI keep getting the follow error after a few hours of running a light node. This happens on both mainnet and ropsten nodes, with an identical stacktrace (minus arguments).\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [09-27|02:09:33.807] Imported new block headers               count=192  elapsed=793.052ms number=8759832 hash=\"dcbb17â€¦dcfc96\" age=15h4m44s\r\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\n[signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x1c0 pc=0xda5a78]\r\n\r\ngoroutine 70 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).reorgOnNewHead(0xc002eaf4a0, 0x1520660, 0xc002730ae0, 0xc002f37440, 0xc002730ae0, 0xc002ee29d0, 0x4664ac)\r\n        github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:229 +0x238\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).setNewHead(0xc002eaf4a0, 0xc002f37440)\r\n        github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:310 +0xf7\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).eventLoop(0xc002eaf4a0)\r\n        github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:291 +0x56\r\ncreated by github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.NewTxPool\r\n        github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:108 +0x3da\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Create a free tier instance on AWS EC2.\r\n\r\n2. Open ports in the firewall.\r\n\r\n3. Log in and start a node with:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncd geth-linux-amd64-1.9.21-0287d548/\r\n\r\n./geth --syncmode light \\\r\n  --datadir \"$HOME/.ethereum-mainnet\" \\\r\n  --port 30303 \\\r\n  --cache 32 \\\r\n  --rpc --rpcaddr 172.31.42.120 --rpcport 28545 --rpcapi personal,web3,eth \\\r\n  --ws --wsaddr 172.31.42.120 --wsport 28546 --wsapi personal,web3,eth\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, I'm going to try downgrading to an earlier version that worked for me in the past.\r\n\r\nUpdate: I downgraded to geth-linux-amd64-1.9.17-748f22c1 and have not encountered the same problem.",
